普通生物學甲課程大綱








 1. Campbell Biology, Jane B. Reece, et al., 2013. 10th ed., Pearson/ Benjamin Cummings.
 2. Biological Science, Scott Freeman, 2013, 5th ed., Pearson/ Benjamin Cummings.
 3. Biology, Peter. H. Raven, et al., 2013, 10th ed., The McGraw-Hill Higher Education.
 4. Biology: the dynamic science, Peter J., Russell, et al., 2014, 3rd ed., Cengage Learning.
 5. Biology: the unity and diversity of life, Cecie Starr, et al., 2013, 13th ed., Cengage Learning.
 6. Campbell Biology in Focus, Lisa A. Urry, et al., AP 1st ed., 2014, Pearson/ Benjamin Cummings.
 7. Biology, Robert Brooker, et al., 2014, 3rd ed., The McGraw-Hill Higher Education.
 8. Biology, Eldra Solomon, et al., 2014, 10th ed., Cengage Learning.











Introduction to Biology - The Secret of Life
Eric Lander et. al. (English)
Explore the secret of life through the basics of biochemistry, genetics, molecular biology, recombinant DNA, genomics and rational medicine.






UC Berkeley Biology courses
Webcast.berkeley is UC Berkeley's central service for online video & audio for students and learners around the globe.






Introduction to Biology
Dr. Claudette Gardel, Prof. Eric Lander, Prof. Robert Weinberg, and Prof. Andrew Chess (English)
This course which is one of the MIT Biology Department core courses focuses on the exploration of current research in cell biology, immunology, neurobiology, genomics, and molecular medicine.






Introductory Biology
Prof. Graham Walker, Dr. Julia Khodor, Dr. Michelle Mischke, and Prof. Penny Chisholm (English)
This course which is one of the MIT Biology Department core courses focuses on the application of these fundamental principles, toward an understanding of microorganisms as geochemical agents responsible for the evolution and renewal of the biosphere and of their role in human health and disease.










